-- Iran finance minister: country's FX reserves are in good position
-- 
-- Fri Oct 12, 2012 2:42am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/12/us-imf-economy-iran-idUSBRE89B0AU20121012

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Iran's finance minister said on Friday that despite sanctions imposed on the country by Western nations, Iran's foreign exchange reserves are in a "good position". 
 Shamseddin Hosseini, Iran's minister of economic affairs and finance, told reporters the government was taking steps to curb speculative demand and other measures to combat a sharp decline in Iran's rial. Hosseini was in Tokyo to attend meetings of the International Monetary Fund. (Reporting by Stanley White; Writing by  Chris Gallagher ; Editing by Edmund Klamann)